Executive Profile
Nicholas J. Valeriani  Chief Executive and Manager, The West Health Investment FundAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 6 Board Members in 6 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships60--
Background

		Mr. Nicholas J. Valeriani, also known as Nick, serves as the Chief Executive and Manager of The West Health Investment Fund. Mr. Valeriani served as the Chief Executive at West Health since 2012. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of The Gary and Mary West Health Institute from 2012 to September 2015. In this role, he had valuable expertise in engineering, operations, medical devices and diagnostics, entrepreneurship and non-profit leadership that make him uniquely ... qualified to advance the mission to lower health care costs through the West Health Institute, West Health Policy Center, West Health Investment Fund and West Health Incubator. He established himself as a visionary healthcare leader over a 34-year career with Johnson & Johnson which he joined in 1978 and led several corporate functions. He served as the Vice President of Strategy & Growth at Johnson & Johnson from January 2008 to 2009, Group Chairman and served as its Group Chairman of Ortho-Clinical Diagnostics from 2009 to 2012. He served as the Corporate Vice President of Human Resources at Johnson & Johnson from September 2003 to 2004, Worldwide Chairman of Diagnostic since February 2004 and Worldwide Chairman of Medical Devices Group since 2006. He served as the Head of Office of Strategy and Growth at Johnson & Johnson since January 2008 and also served as its Worldwide Chairman of Cardiovascular Devices & Diagnostics since January 2005. He was instrumental in identifying the global healthcare trends that led to the creation of a new wellness and prevention business platform and pioneering opportunities in the area of digital health. He served as the President of Ethicon Endo-Surgery Inc., since 1997. He serves as the Chairman of the Board of Sense4Baby, Inc. He has been the Director at RTI Surgical, Inc. since June 2016. He has been an Independent Director of Edwards Lifesciences Corp. since November 13, 2014 and Roka Bioscience, Inc. since August 2015. He serves as a Director of Change Healthcare Corporation and The Gary and Mary West Health Institute. He serves on the Board of Directors for the Robert Wood Johnson University Hospital, Action Healthy Kids and AdvaMed. Since January 2001, he served as Group Chairman for Ethicon Endo-Surgery with additional responsibility for Johnson & Johnson Medical Products Medical Devices and Diagnostics business. He served as the Worldwide Franchise Chairman for the DePuy Franchise since 2002. He serves on the Boards of Directors of the Reagan-Udall Foundation, Reflexion Health, Inc., and the Center for Medical Interoperability. He served as a Member of the Board of Directors at The West Health Investment Fund. Mr. Valeriani holds an MBA from Rutgers University, Graduate School of Management and a Bachelor of Science Degree in Industrial Engineering from Rutgers University, College of Engineering.Read Full Background




